    "enDesc": "Likkutei HaPardes is a collection of legal material attributed to Rashi (Rabbi Shlomo ben Yitzchak) and is part of a body of literature known as Sifrei DeVei Rashi (Works of the School of Rashi), compiled by Rashi’s students. The first such collection to be published (1519), Likkutei HaPardes includes much of the same content as the longer Sefer HaPardes, which was not published until 1807. The collection is arranged topically and includes laws related to marriage, blessings, the Kaddish prayer, visiting the sick, holidays, and Torah readings.",
    "enShortDesc": "Early medieval collection of legal material relating to a variety of topics, attributed to Rashi and compiled by his students.",
